1. Clustering

  • sub-group, (cluster)

  • 2

    • K- (K-Means Clustering)

    • (Hierarchical Clustering)

1.1

  • (similarity)

    • Euclidean: quantitative \[ d(x, y) = \sqrt{\sum_{j=1}^d(x_j - y_j)^2} \]

    • Hamming distance (number of mismatches): categorical \[ d(x, y) = \sum_{j=1}^d I(x_j \neq y_j) \]

    • Manhattan (city block) distance: quantitative \[ d(x, y) = \sum_{j=1}^d |x_j - y_j| \]


1.2 K- K-means clustering

K-means

  • \(\{x_i,\,i=1,2,...,n\}\), \(\{c_1, c_2,...,c_k\}\) .

  1. \(K\) \(\{z_k,\,k=1,2,...,K\}\)

  2. \(x_i\) (\(i=1,2,...,n\))

  4. \(z_k\) (\(k=1,2,...,K\))

  5. 2

  • \[\sum_{i=1}^n \sum_{k=1}^K I(x_i\in c_k)d(x_i, z_k)\] ,

  • , 1

  • \(K\)-means .

: 

set.seed(0)
x <- rbind(matrix(rnorm(100, sd = 0.3), ncol = 2),
           matrix(rnorm(100, mean = 1, sd = 0.3), ncol = 2))
colnames(x) <- c("x", "y")
cl <- kmeans(x, 2)
par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
plot(x, xlab = "", ylab = "", col = "gray", pch = 19, 
     main = "Original data")
color <- cl$cluster + 1
plot(x, xlab = "", ylab = "", col = color, pch = 19, 
     main = "Clustered data")
points(cl$centers, col = 2:3, pch = "+", cex = 2)

pKmeans <- kmeans(pmat, 5) 
print.clusters <- function(labels, k) {
  for(i in 1:k) {
    print(paste("cluster", i))
    print(protein[labels == i, c("Country","RedMeat","Fish","Fr.Veg")])
  }
}

1.3 Hierarchical clustering

  • hierarchy dendrogram

: protein

d <- dist(pmat, method = "euclidean") # Euclidean distances
pfit <- hclust(d, method = "ward.D2")
  • dendrogram 
plot(pfit, labels = protein$Country)
rect.hclust(pfit, k = 5)


2. Density estimation

2.1 Parametric

  • : . () .

    • (c.f.)

  • Maximum likelihood estimation

    • \(x_1,x_2,...,x_n\) \(f(x|\theta)\) likelihood \[ L(\theta|x_1,...,x_n) = \prod_{i=1}^n f(x_i|\theta) \]

    • \(L(\theta|x_1,...,x_n)\) \(\log L(\theta|x_1,...,x_n)\) \(\theta\) : MLE, maximum likelihood estimation

2.2 Nonparametric: Kernel smoothing

  • ,

    • \(x_1, ..., x_n\) \(f(x)\) , \[ \hat f (x) = \frac{1}{nh}\sum_{i=1}^n K \left(\frac{x_i - x}{h}\right) \] , \(K\) , \(h\) (bandwidth).

    • \(K\) \(h\) 

data(faithful)

par(mfrow = c(1, 2))

hist(faithful$eruptions, probability = TRUE, 
     xlim = c(0, 7), main = "", col = "gray", border = "white", xlab = "Eruptions")
rug(faithful$eruptions)
lines(density(faithful$eruptions), col = 2, lwd = 3)

hist(faithful$eruptions, probability = TRUE, nclass = 20, 
     xlim = c(0, 7), main = "", col = "gray", border = "white", xlab = "Eruptions")
rug(faithful$eruptions)
lines(density(faithful$eruptions), col = 2, lwd = 3)


3. Dimension reduction

3.1 Principal Component Analysis, PCA

  • Feature ()

  • PCA feature () .



  • \(N\times J\) \(X\) \(\Sigma\) spectral decomposition (\(N > J\)) \[ \Sigma = P \Lambda P^\top = \sum_{j=1}^J \lambda_j p_j p_j^\top \]

    • , \(P = [p_1, p_2,...,p_J]\) \(\Sigma\) \(\lambda_j\)(\(\lambda_1\ge \lambda_2\ge...\) ) \(p_j\) . \(p_j\) .

  • feature

    • PCA

3.2 FA, factor analysis

  • Feature PCA , FA feature (latent factor)

  • , feature .



  • \(X = (X_1,X_2,...,X_p)^\top\sim \cdot(0_p,\Sigma)\) , \[X = LF + \epsilon \quad(p \ge m)\]

    • \(F\) \[ \textsf{E}(F) = 0_m,\quad \textsf{Var}(F) = I_m \]

    • (unique factor) \(\epsilon\) \[ \textsf{E}(\epsilon) = 0_p,\quad \textsf{Var}(\epsilon) = \Psi = \textsf{diag}(\psi_1,...,\psi_p) \] \[ \textsf{Cov}(\epsilon, F) = O_{(p\times m)} \]


  • \[ \Sigma = L L^\top + \Psi,\quad \textsf{Cov}(X, F) = L \] , \(L\) \(T\) \(L^* = LT\) ( ).

  • \(L\) \(\Psi\) \(F\) (factor score) .

  • feature

  • Confirmatory factor analysis(CFA), exploratory factor analysis , CFA

3.3 ICA, independent component analysis

  • PCA

  • Factor analysis non-normal

  • (whitened) \(X = (X_1,X_2,...,X_n)^\top\) \(q\) \(S_1, ..., S_q\) \[ X = AS = \left[a_1\, a_2\, \cdots a_q \right] \left[\begin{array}{c} S_1 \\ S_2 \\ \vdots \\ S_q \end{array} \right] = \sum_{j=1}^q a_j S_j \]

    • \(S_j\)

    • \(A\)

  • \(X\)


: 

S <- cbind(sin((1:1000)/20), rep((((1:200)-100)/100), 5))
A <- matrix(c(0.291, 0.6557, -0.5439, 0.5572), 2, 2)
X <- S %*% A
dim(X)
## [1] 1000    2
A # mixing matrix to estimate
##        [,1]    [,2]
## [1,] 0.2910 -0.5439
## [2,] 0.6557  0.5572
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
plot(1:1000, S[,1], type = "l", main = "Original source signal 1", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, S[,2], type = "l", main = "Original source signal 2",
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, X[,1], type = "l", main = "Mixed signal 1 (channel 1)", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, X[,2], type = "l", main = "Mixed signal 2 (channel 2)", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)

  • ICA

    • fastICA fastICA() 
library(fastICA)
a <- fastICA(X, 2)
par(mfrow = c(3, 2))
plot(1:1000, S[,1], type = "l", main = "Original source signal 1", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, S[,2], type = "l", main = "Original source signal 2",
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, X[,1], type = "l", main = "Mixed signal 1 (channel 1)", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, X[,2], type = "l", main = "Mixed signal 2 (channel 2)", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, a$S[,1], type = "l", main = "ICA source estimates 1", 
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)
plot(1:1000, a$S[,2], type = "l", main = "ICA source estimates 2",
     xlab = "", ylab = "",
     cex.main = 0.8, cex.axis = 0.7)

4. Multiple testing


  • , , conversion rate feature

  • Hypotheses: \(H_{0,1}, H_{0,2},...,H_{0,N}\)

  • Corresponding \(z\)-values: \(z_1,...,z_N\)

  • Problem: \(z_i\) threshold?

  • Testing

    {} Action: NULL Action: NONNULL Sum
    Truth: NULL \(a\) \(b\) \(a + b\)
    Truth: NONNULL \(c\) \(d\) \(c + d\)
    Sum \(a + c\) \(b + d\) \(N = a+b+c+d\)
  • FWER vs.FDR

    • Familywise error rate: \(P(b > 0)\)

      • Bonferroni correction: , \(\alpha' = \alpha/N\)

      • Random field theory

    • FDR: \(E(b/(b + d))\)
